ers fan art, and as they're a futuristic firefighting team, not being able to draw flames obviously limits the situations I can put them in! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
It's difficult to describe the main problems I come across. When drawing fire, it always looks too flat and two-dimesional - I don't know how to give the flames depth. They just look like cardboard cutouts sticking out of the floor.<br>
<br>
When drawing explosions, they never look really powerful or dramatic - they just look like simple fluffy clouds with speed-lines radiating out of them.<br>
<br>
Would you need an example of my work in order to advise me? If so, I'll be happy to post something, though I don't think I've got anything online at the moment. But if anyone has any advice on how to improve, I'd be very grateful!  <p>---<br>
